  "text": "Remark 2. Since the solution [CITATION_1] and (8) of [CITATION_2] is always feasible for the constraints [CITATION_3] , it follows that the achievable communication load L(q) in (11) is always no larger than that in [CITATION_4] . This is because the load (11) with r 1 and r 2 in (7)- [CITATION_5] is no larger than the load in [11, eq. (9) ]. To demonstrate that the improvement can be strict, beside the example given in Section 4, we provide next a numerical example.",
